'''Kanizawa Kofun''' (蟹沢古墳) may refer to the following Kofuns (kofun) in Japan:
* '''{{ill|Kanizawa Kofun (Nakano, Nagano)|ja|蟹沢古墳 (中野市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanizawa Kofun (Nakano, Nagano)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}''' – A kofun located in '''Nakano, Nagano Prefecture'''. It is a '''designated historic site of Nakano City'''. * '''{{ill|Shibasaki Kanizawa Kofun|ja|柴崎蟹沢古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibasaki Kanizawa Kofun|qq=}}''' – A kofun formerly located in '''Takasaki, Gunma Prefecture'''. Artifacts excavated from the site, including a '''mirrored inscription dated "□ Shigen Year" (□始元年)''', are '''designated as National Important Cultural Properties of Japan'''.
[[zh-yue:神戸市]]
